To resolve the error and synchronize your database with the new payment tracking features, please run the following SQL commands in your **Supabase SQL Editor**:

```sql
-- 1. Add paid_amount to transactions (Tracks actual cash collected per item)
ALTER TABLE transactions 
ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS paid_amount numeric DEFAULT 0;

-- 2. Add payment_status to transactions (Tracks if it's PAID, PARTIAL, or PENDING)
ALTER TABLE transactions 
ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS payment_status text DEFAULT 'PAID';

-- 3. Add paid_amount to invoices (For printed tax invoices)
ALTER TABLE invoices 
ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS paid_amount numeric DEFAULT 0;

-- 4. Update existing records to ensure they aren't NULL
UPDATE transactions SET paid_amount = (price * quantity) WHERE paid_amount IS NULL AND payment_status = 'PAID';
UPDATE transactions SET paid_amount = 0 WHERE paid_amount IS NULL;
UPDATE invoices SET paid_amount = total_amount WHERE paid_amount IS NULL;

-- 5. Notify the PostgREST cache to refresh (Optional but recommended)
NOTIFY pgrst, 'reload schema';
```

### Why this happened:
The "schema cache" error occurs when the frontend code tries to send or receive data for a column (`paid_amount`) that doesn't yet exist in your physical database tables. Running the `ALTER TABLE` commands above creates those columns so the API can recognize them.

**Note:** After running the SQL, if the error persists, simply refresh your browser tab to ensure the frontend is also in sync with the new schema.

